                  <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2">
                    <tr>
                      <td height="25"><font size="3">Nauru</font></td>
                      <td align="right"> <font size="3"><img src="../../img/flags/flg_nauru.gif" width="70" height="35"></font></td>
                    </tr>
                  </table>
                  <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" height="1">
                    <tr background="../../img/maps/cp_tile.gif" valign="top"> 
                      <td background="../../img/maps/cp_tile.gif"><img src="../../img/maps/cp_space.gif" width="37" height="1"></td>
                    </tr>
                  </table>
                  <p class="profile_intro"><img src="../../img/maps/cp_nauru.gif" width="293" height="182" align="right">Nauru, 
                    the smallest independent republic in the world, has one of 
                    the highest GDP/capita amongst independent Pacific states. 
                    But this prosperity has come at a price. After decades of 
                    phosphate mining, 90% of the island now needs rehabilitating. 
                  <p><br>
                    <br>
                    </p><br>
                  <h5><a name="facts"></a>Facts and Figures</h5>
